🦁 Heracles/Nemean Lion 🐆  Yes I know that other coin is a cheetah, but I wanted to include the epic murrini coin in the photo 😆 The mythological Greek story about Heracles slaying the Nemean Lion is the reason Heracles is depicted wearing a lion-skin headdress on these ancient coins. Top coin is a silver drachm from around 336-323 BC with Zeus seated on the reverse & the bottom coin is a Roman Republic AE quadrans showing a massive galley prow on the reverse. #ancientart • #ancientcoin • #ancientcoins • #murrini • #murrine • #millefiori • #murriniofig • #headyart
